different way, we're gonna like use some other, you know, tokens, whatever, to make that that

00:26:25.920 --> 00:26:30.719
access more secure. And the users never knew, right? Like, it's because it's just basically

00:26:30.719 --> 00:26:33.920
like, we've thought about their experience. And like, part of their experience is like,

00:26:33.920 --> 00:26:38.319
they should never have to learn a new database connection algorithm. Like, they shouldn't need

00:26:38.319 --> 00:26:45.359
