which we use. I wouldn't say we do anything particularly interesting with it, but it's

00:54:11.679 --> 00:54:16.320
useful. I've had a good experience with all of those. These aren't the only tools that we use,

00:54:16.320 --> 00:54:21.360
and these aren't the only sort of layers of security. Like, there's this idea called defense

00:54:21.360 --> 00:54:26.320
in depth with security, as you want, like, just many, many layers. But we do use both of those,

00:54:26.320 --> 00:54:30.159
and I've been very happy with them. Does that answer your question?

